.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH ecd-encodings 1  "encodings " 
.SH NAME
ecd\-encodings \- List valid encoding names
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBecd encodings\fR [\fB\-\-color\fR] [\fB\-l\fR|\fB\-\-list\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
List valid encoding names
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR \fI<WHEN>\fR [default: never]
When to colorize encoding labels (`[UTF\-8]`, `[SKIP]`, …) in batch output
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto: Colorize when stdout is a terminal and `NO_COLOR` is unset
.IP \(bu 2
never: Never colorize (default)
.IP \(bu 2
always: Always colorize (ANSI escapes; useful for piping to `less \-R`)
.RE
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-list\fR
List valid encoding names (default action)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
